    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Giuliani Internalized</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter form Skip Blumberg says James Traub's Feb 11 article praising Mayor Rudolph W Giuliani failed to mention unfriendliness emanating from Giuliani's City Hall</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The locked gates to City Hall Park are not a legacy. They are an impermanent policy (and a metaphor for Giuliani's approach to our municipal democracy). The next, more egalitarian mayor will correct this policy. What will remain is our memory of the unfriendliness emanating from Giuliani's City Hall.</p>
        <p>Skip Blumberg  New York</p>
      </block>
